  Two metrics, based respectively on k -OPT and 2-OPT, for measuring the distance between traveling salesman tours are considered and their relationship worked out. [1] D.S. Johnson Local optimization and the travelling salesman problem Proceedings of the 17th Colloquium on Automata, Languages and Programming, Springer, Berlin (1990), pp. 446–461 [2] S. Lin, B.W. Kernighan An effective heuristic algorithm for the travelling-salesman problem Oper. Res., 21 (1973), pp. 498–516 [3] K.-T. Mak, A.J. Morton A modified Lin-Kernighan travelling-salesman heuristic Oper. Res. Lett., 13 (1993), pp. 127–132 [4] M. Padberg, G. Rinaldi A branch-and-cut algorithm for the resolution of large-scale symmetric traveling salesman problems SIAM Rev., 33 (1991), pp. 60–100 Copyright © 1995 Published by Elsevier B.V.